### HA-Aware Migration

When changing the <span pulumi-lang-nodejs="`nodeName`" pulumi-lang-dotnet="`NodeName`" pulumi-lang-go="`nodeName`" pulumi-lang-python="`node_name`" pulumi-lang-yaml="`nodeName`" pulumi-lang-java="`nodeName`">`nodeName`</span> of an HA-managed VM, the provider automatically
handles the migration in an HA-aware manner:

- **Running HA VMs**: Uses the HA manager's migrate endpoint for live migration
- **Stopped HA VMs**: Temporarily removes from HA, performs standard migration,
  then re-adds to HA with the original configuration preserved

> **PVE 9.x Required**: HA-aware migration requires Proxmox VE 9.x due to API
changes. On PVE 8.x, migrating HA-managed VMs will fail. As a workaround,
manually remove the VM from HA before changing <span pulumi-lang-nodejs="`nodeName`" pulumi-lang-dotnet="`NodeName`" pulumi-lang-go="`nodeName`" pulumi-lang-python="`node_name`" pulumi-lang-yaml="`nodeName`" pulumi-lang-java="`nodeName`">`nodeName`</span>, then re-add after
